# Scripts

## Conventions

- Use `#!/usr/bin/env bash` shebang and `set -euo pipefail`
- Scripts must work on both macOS and Linux (use `$(nproc)` with `sysctl -n hw.ncpu` fallback)
- Document usage in a comment at the top of the file
- Exit with non-zero on failure — CI depends on exit codes

## Wiring

New scripts should be wired into at least one of:
- `package.json` scripts (for npm-based checks)
- `.githooks/pre-commit` or `.githooks/pre-push` (for local enforcement)
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (for CI enforcement)

Document which hook/CI job runs the script in a comment at the top.

